    {
        "content": "<p>Heap-Hop <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/12778#issuecomment-4062746754\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/12778\">issue #12778</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Heap-Hop/wasmtime/actions/runs/23099865150\">https://github.com/Heap-Hop/wasmtime/actions/runs/23099865150</a><br>\nCI passed and it works fine on Android.</p>\n<p>The changes were suggested by AI, and I'm not very familiar with this area, so they definitely need review.</p>\n<p>Should I open a PR for this, or would someone else like to start one based on this attempt?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 579536950,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1773571356
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>cfallin <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/12778#issuecomment-4063506829\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/12778\">issue #12778</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Thanks for filing the issue. Looking at the diff you liked, the fundamental bug appears to be that we don't conditionalize use of pointer-authentication instructions on target features, as you say. Cranelift-compiled code will work fine because we have <code>cranelift-native</code> that does feature detection; but the fiber-switch routines are hardcoded.</p>\n<p>That said, the diff has kind of made a mess of the code -- it removes the <code>cfg_if</code> entirely and messes up the logic. Could you (human, not LLM) refactor the patch so that it retains the <code>cfg_if</code>, and splits the <code>else</code> branch into <code>else if (pac features) { existing non-Apple defs } else { empty defs }</code>? I think we'd be happy to review a patch with that. Thanks!</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 579564727,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1773597298
    }
]